<section id="about" class="fade-in">
  <span class="sec-lbl" id="lAbout">About Mizoram</span>
  <h2 class="sec-title" id="aboutTitle">Jewel of <em>Northeast India</em></h2>
  <p class="sec-body" id="aboutBody">Mizoram, literally "Land of the Blue Mountains," is a picturesque hill state in Northeast India representing untouched natural beauty and vibrant tribal culture. Known for its rolling hills, bamboo forests, serene valleys and pristine rivers, Mizoram showcases nature's finest artwork. The state is home to warm-hearted tribal communities preserving ancient traditions through music, dance and crafts. From the bustling capital Aizawl perched on hillsides to remote villages maintaining age-old customs, Mizoram offers authentic tribal experiences. The state's exceptional biodiversity, environmental consciousness, and sustainable living practices make it a beacon of responsible tourism. With the highest literacy rate in India and strong community bonds, Mizoram represents Northeast India's progressive spirit while honoring its rich tribal heritage.</p>
